\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The same coupling, two implementations. \textbf  {(a)} The complete graph $K_6$: agents pool each other's opinions directly. This is Eq.~\eqref  {eq:pairwise}; the ``field'' exists only as each agent's private, instantaneous weighted mean. \textbf  {(b)} A single shared field node $f$ mediates all coupling (Eq.~\eqref  {eq:fast}--\eqref  {eq:slow}): agents \emph  {deposit} into it (inward, blue) and \emph  {read} from it (outward, orange). Reading the field is the act of attending to the collective. The field is slow ($\tau _f\!\gg \!1$) and is the only object that carries collective state between steps.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:motif}{{1}{2}{The same coupling, two implementations. \textbf {(a)} The complete graph $K_6$: agents pool each other's opinions directly. This is Eq.~\eqref {eq:pairwise}; the ``field'' exists only as each agent's private, instantaneous weighted mean. \textbf {(b)} A single shared field node $f$ mediates all coupling (Eq.~\eqref {eq:fast}--\eqref {eq:slow}): agents \emph {deposit} into it (inward, blue) and \emph {read} from it (outward, orange). Reading the field is the act of attending to the collective. The field is slow ($\tau _f\!\gg \!1$) and is the only object that carries collective state between steps}{figure.1}{}}
