\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces The mediating field across scales. In every case a population of units couples \emph  {only} through a slow shared field they both write ($\rightarrow $ in) and sense ($\rightarrow $ out): transmembrane voltage $V_{\mathrm  {mem}}$ patterning tissue; the pheromone concentration on a trail; the mean activity $\bar  h$ of a competing neural population; the consensus ``power structure''/norm a community references. The topology is identical to Fig.~\ref {fig:motif}b.}}{3}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:fourstars}{{2}{3}{The mediating field across scales. In every case a population of units couples \emph {only} through a slow shared field they both write ($\rightarrow $ in) and sense ($\rightarrow $ out): transmembrane voltage $V_{\mathrm {mem}}$ patterning tissue; the pheromone concentration on a trail; the mean activity $\bar h$ of a competing neural population; the consensus ``power structure''/norm a community references. The topology is identical to Fig.~\ref {fig:motif}b}{figure.2}{}}
